\begin_layout Standard
One of the original design goals of the microeactors was that the reactors
 should have a high sensitivity to able to measure on very small amounts
 of catalyst.
 However, during the measurements on the oscillations, we relized that we
 were able to reach full conversion on sample with even very small amounts
 of catalyst.
 At some point we realized that it would be interesting to test how small
 amount of catalyst we can actually get to full conversion.
 To test the sensitivity we have performed of series of tests using CO oxidation
 on Pt thin films as the test reaction.
